00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:07.500
Hello, and welcome to the
BC First Nations Justice Council.

00:00:07.500 --> 00:00:12.000
My name is [Presenter Name], and I'm here
to walk you through everything you need

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.500
to get started with your technology at BCFNJC.

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:20.000
In this video, we'll cover your laptop setup,
how to care for and secure your device,

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.500
how to reach IT support, and a guided tour
of the Microsoft 365 tools

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:27.000
you'll use every day.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:32.500
Whether you're brand new to Microsoft 365 or just
need to get familiar with how we do things here,

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:36.000
this video is your guide. Let's get started.

NOTE Scene 02 — Hardware Overview

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.000
Let's start with your laptop.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:48.500
You'll notice there's a small physical privacy
shutter on your webcam.

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:54.000
Get in the habit of sliding it closed whenever
you're not on a video call.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.500
It's a simple way to protect your privacy.

00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:03.000
For best performance, keep your laptop
plugged in when you're at your desk.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.500
And whenever possible, connect
using an Ethernet cable.

00:01:08.500 --> 00:01:14.000
Wired connections are faster and more stable
than Wi-Fi — especially for video calls

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.000
and large file transfers.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:22.500
Finally — please reboot your laptop
at least once every few days.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:28.000
This keeps everything running smoothly and makes
sure important security updates get installed.

NOTE Scene 03 — Care & Security

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:15.000
Taking good care of your device also means
taking care of the people we serve.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:20.500
When you're traveling with your laptop,
keep it in a secure bag

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:24.000
and never leave it unattended in a car
or public space.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:29.500
If your device is ever lost, stolen, or damaged —
even a cracked screen —

00:02:29.500 --> 00:02:32.500
please notify IT immediately.

00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:38.000
The faster we know, the faster we can protect
your account and our organization's data.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Protecting our clients' information is something
we all take seriously here.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:49.500
Please be thoughtful about where you use your
laptop and who can see your screen.

00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:55.000
For personal use, please keep it to a minimum
and stay within our Acceptable Use Policy,

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
which you can find on the Intranet.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:05.000
If you have travel coming up that might involve
exceptions to standard policy, reach out to IT

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:08.000
in advance — we're happy to help.

NOTE Scene 04 — IT Support

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:30.000
If you ever run into a technical issue,
we make it easy to get help.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:35.500
Your first stop should be the Intranet — it has
answers to the most common questions,

00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:39.000
along with IT forms and policies.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:44.500
If you need direct support, you can email us
at support@sfy.ca,

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:49.000
or call 1-877-378-6730.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:54.000
We're here Monday through Friday and we'll
get back to you as quickly as possible.

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.500
Don't hesitate to reach out —
that's what we're here for.

NOTE Scene 05 — Hardware & Printers

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:21.000
If you ever need additional hardware —
a monitor, a keyboard, a headset —

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:25.000
start by talking to your manager.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:30.500
They'll work with IT to make sure
you have what you need.

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:36.000
Your laptop comes with antivirus and endpoint
protection software already installed.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:41.500
You don't need to do anything to set that up —
it's running in the background keeping you safe.

00:04:41.500 --> 00:04:47.000
For printers: once you're connected to the staff
network, reach out to SFY to have a printer

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:50.500
deployed to your device.

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:56.000
It typically appears in your printer list
within 10 to 15 minutes. Easy.

NOTE Scene 06 — Microsoft Edge & Intranet

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:20.500
Microsoft Edge is the browser we use at BCFNJC.

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:26.000
Once you sign in with your Microsoft 365 account,
your bookmarks, passwords, and browser settings

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:30.000
will sync automatically across any device you use.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:35.500
Your first stop online should be the Intranet.
It's your central hub for everything BCFNJC —

00:05:35.500 --> 00:05:41.000
staff directories, organizational resources,
IT forms, and our Acceptable Use Policy.

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:45.000
Bookmark it now so it's always one click away.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:51.000
You'll also have access to BCFNJC's SharePoint
environment, where shared documents

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.000
and resources are stored.

NOTE Scene 07 — OneDrive & File Management

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:40.000
OneDrive is where your files live — and it's
working for you automatically in the background.

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:45.500
Your Desktop, Documents, and Pictures folders
are all backed up to OneDrive.

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:50.000
So if anything happens to your laptop,
your files are safe in the cloud.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:56.000
You'll see a small green checkmark icon next to
files and folders in File Explorer —

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
that means they're synced and backed up.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:05.500
If you have questions about where to store
specific records or documents,

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:09.000
reach out to records@bcfnjc.com.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:14.500
And when you need to access or share
organizational files with colleagues,

00:07:14.500 --> 00:07:19.000
the BCFNJC SharePoint shared library
is where you'll find them.

NOTE Scene 08 — Outlook Email

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:54.000
Outlook is your email and calendar home base.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:08:00.000
When you first open it, take a few minutes
to explore the address book.

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:05.500
You'll find all BCFNJC staff listed there, along
with distribution lists for teams and departments —

00:08:05.500 --> 00:08:10.000
which makes it easy to send messages
to the right group of people.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:16.000
To confirm your email is set up correctly,
send a quick test email.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:21.500
Your Outlook calendar is where you'll schedule
meetings, accept meeting invites,

00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:25.000
and check colleagues' availability.

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:30.500
Make sure to subscribe to the All Staff calendar —
it's listed in the calendar sidebar —

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:36.000
so you stay informed about organization-wide
events and closures.

NOTE Scene 09 — Microsoft Teams

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:25.500
Microsoft Teams is where the day-to-day
collaboration happens at BCFNJC.

00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:31.000
Once you've signed in, go to your settings
and enable auto-launch.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:36.500
That way, Teams will start automatically every
time you log into your computer,

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:40.000
and you'll never miss a message or meeting.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:46.000
Next, head into your notification settings and
make sure you have notifications turned on

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:49.000
for the All Staff team.

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:55.000
This keeps you connected with
organization-wide updates.

00:09:55.000 --> 00:10:01.000
Teams is also your tool for video and audio
meetings, screen sharing, and sharing files

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:04.000
within your team channels.

NOTE Scene 10 — Microsoft Word & Templates

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:46.000
When you create a document at BCFNJC, always
start with one of our organizational templates.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:51.500
Open Microsoft Word, go to File, then New,
and you'll see a section for BCFNJC templates.

00:10:51.500 --> 00:10:57.000
These are pre-formatted with our branding,
fonts, and layouts.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:02.500
Our default font is Montserrat. Please use it
in all documents you create.

00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:08.000
When it comes to saving: always save
your files to OneDrive.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:13.500
When you do, AutoSave activates automatically —
which means Word is saving your work

00:11:13.500 --> 00:11:17.000
every few seconds as you type.

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:23.000
Before you edit any template, save a personal
copy first so the original stays intact

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:25.500
for everyone else.

NOTE Scene 11 — Adobe Acrobat Pro

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:56.000
For working with PDFs, you have Adobe
Acrobat Pro installed on your device.

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:02.000
You can use it to view, edit, annotate, and
digitally sign PDF documents —

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:07.000
which comes up regularly for contracts,
forms, and official correspondence.

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:13.000
If you're new to Acrobat, don't worry — there
are resources on the Intranet to help you.

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:17.000
And of course, IT is always here
if you have questions.

NOTE Scene 12 — Closing

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:40.000
And that's your IT onboarding overview.

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:45.500
You've covered a lot of ground today — from
your hardware setup to Microsoft 365,

00:12:45.500 --> 00:12:49.000
file management, and collaboration tools.

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:54.500
If you missed anything or want to revisit a
section, this video is available anytime

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:58.000
on the BCFNJC SharePoint intranet.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:04.000
Remember — your Intranet is your first stop
for answers. And our IT team

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:10.000
at support@sfy.ca or 1-877-378-6730
is always here when you need us.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:17.000
Welcome to BCFNJC. We're really glad you're
here, and we look forward to working with you.
